# .aidocs/memory-system.aidocs - Global Memory Protocol

Purpose
- Keep reusable project knowledge in files, not transient chat context.

Location
- Runtime memory lives in project-root `/.MEMORY/`.
- Entry files (`AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`) are routers, not memory stores.

Structure
- `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`
- `/.MEMORY/rules/standards.md`
- `/.MEMORY/rules/security.md`
- `/.MEMORY/system/architecture.md`
- `/.MEMORY/system/caveats.md`
- `/.MEMORY/system/decisions.md`
- `/.MEMORY/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md`
- `/.MEMORY/daily/archive/`

Runtime
- Not init-only.
- On material state changes, update `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`.
- Log notable outcomes in today's daily file.
- Before final coding response, checkpoint `Goal | State | Next`.

Capture
- If user states a durable fact/rule/lesson/preference, persist immediately to the right categorized file and log daily.

Archive
- `/archive` promotes durable signal from active daily logs into categorized files.
- Merge/edit existing entries (no duplicate append-only content).
- Use `Supersedes:` when replacing prior guidance.
- Move processed logs to `/.MEMORY/daily/archive/`.

Template-first
- Initialize memory from `.aidocs/templates/memory/**` (copy missing files), then merge extracted guidance.

Retrieval order
1) `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`
2) relevant categorized files (`rules/*`, `system/*`)
3) targeted daily snippets only when needed

Guardrails
- Never store secrets/sensitive data.
- Do not promote speculation or one-off noise.
- If memory conflicts with code/docs, record conflict and propose resolution.
